  "text": "\u00de represents the colour distance between the colour distribution of the pixels in vpm\u00f0 x ! \u00de and the colour model of the person (see Section 4.3). A popular approach for measuring the similarity of two distributions is the Bhattacharyya distance [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The Bhattacharyya distance of two colour histograms q 1 and q 2 is calculated as:",
